The paper discusses a meta-learning framework for time-series forecasting, which involves training a neural network on a source dataset and deploying it on a different target dataset without retraining. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses theoretical analysis and adaptation mechanisms, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI) or optimization and learning (cs.LO).
